@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@
+# WebPolicyHandlerDetails Object
+
+* `policy` string - The policy family being checked. Can be
+  `content-security-policy`, `permissions-policy`, `document-policy`, or
+  `browser-runtime`.
+* `name` string - The policy directive, policy feature, or runtime policy name.
+  For example, CSP uses names such as `connect-src` and `script-src`,
+  Permissions Policy and Document Policy use names such as `sync-xhr`, and
+  browser runtime policies use names such as `sync-xhr-page-dismissal`.
+* `source` string - Where the policy check was generated. Currently
+  `runtime`.
+* `disposition` string - Whether the check is for an enforcing policy or a
+  report-only policy. Can be `enforce` or `report`.
+* `contextType` string - The JavaScript context type making the check. Can be
+  `frame`, `dedicated-worker`, `shared-worker`, `service-worker`, or
+  `unknown`.
+* `documentUrl` string - The URL of the document or worker context making the
+  check, or an empty string when the URL is not available yet.
+* `documentOrigin` string - The security origin of the document or worker
+  context making the check.
+* `resourceUrl` string - The resource URL being checked, or an empty string
+  when the policy check is not for a specific resource.
+* `message` string - Additional context from the policy check, or an empty
+  string when unavailable.
+* `frame` [WebFrameMain](../web-frame-main.md) (optional) - The frame making
+  the policy check. This is only present for frame-backed checks while the frame
+  still exists.
